# Bookkeeping Pipeline

## Current app (Phase 1 — manual + import)
- OFX bank import, reconciliation, draft → approve → post journals are the live workflow.
- Do not break existing SQLite schema or multi-entity chart without migration.
- Manual categorization and review UI remain valid until automation replaces them.

## Ingestion (all phases)
- Bank webhooks, Plaid sync, and receipt uploads must use **idempotency keys** — no duplicate transactions.
- **Plaid:** Simmons Bank only — reject Lone Star Bank and other institutions; use `plaid-{transaction_id}` as `fitid`; never re-import the same Plaid transaction_id for an entity.
- Offload heavy OCR/LLM categorization to **background jobs** — never block the Express request thread.

## AI categorization (when implemented)
- Require **structured JSON** output (Zod/schema); no free-form-only parsing.
- Every AI suggestion needs `confidence_score` (0–1). Below **0.85** → review queue, not auto-post.
- **Strip PII** (card numbers, SSN, full account numbers) before sending text to external LLM APIs.

## Prohibited
- Hardcoding regional tax rules in core routes — use config/lookup tables.
- Deleting or mutating posted ledger rows — use offsetting entries only.
